## Troubleshooting

### Build Fails with TypeScript Errors
1. Read error carefully - TS errors are usually clear
2. Check if variable is used before declaration → Move it
3. Check for `any` types → Replace with `unknown` or proper type
4. Check hook dependencies → Add missing deps
5. Run `npm run lint:fix` to auto-fix simple issues

### AI Chatbot Says "I Don't Have Enough Context"
1. Check browser console for `[AI UI] Sending UI state:` logs
2. Check Haystack logs for `🔍 Retrieved UI state` logs
3. Verify UI state has `page_type`, `page_summary`, or `page_content`
4. Check `get_enhanced_system_prompt()` is receiving and using UI state
5. Add debug logging if needed

### WebSocket Connection Issues
1. Check Socket.IO client is connecting: Browser console → Network → WS tab
2. Check Haystack service is running: Visit health endpoint
3. Verify CORS settings allow WebSocket connections
4. Check Redis is accessible (UI state storage)

### Tests Failing
1. Read error message carefully
2. Check mocks are set up correctly
3. Verify test data matches expected format
4. Run single test: `npm test -- -t "test name"`
5. Check for async issues (missing `await`)

## File Organization

### Web Frontend
```
src/
├── components/          # Reusable components
│   ├── ai-assistant/   # AI chatbot components
│   ├── ui/             # shadcn/ui components
│   └── ...
├── pages/              # Route pages
│   ├── chat/          # Standalone chat page
│   ├── live-transcribe/ # Live transcription
│   └── ...
├── services/           # API clients and services
│   ├── ai-ui-integration.ts    # AI context management
│   ├── haystack-service.ts     # Haystack client
│   └── gpt-service.ts          # OpenAI direct client
├── hooks/              # Custom React hooks
├── stores/             # Redux stores (legacy, migrating to hooks)
└── configs/            # Configuration files
```

### Haystack Service
```
haystack/
├── main.py                 # FastAPI app, WebSocket handlers
├── tools.py               # AI tool definitions
├── personas.py            # AI persona configurations
├── ui_state_manager.py    # Redis UI state storage
├── haystack_pipeline.py   # LangChain pipeline
├── session_manager.py     # Session management
├── requirements.txt       # Python dependencies
└── startup.sh            # Azure startup script
```

## Important Notes

### Security
- NEVER commit secrets or API keys
- Use environment variables for all config
- Validate all user input on backend
- Use parameterized queries for database
- Implement rate limiting for AI endpoints
- Sanitize all AI responses before displaying

### Performance
- Lazy load heavy components
- Use React.memo for expensive renders
- Debounce user input (especially for AI)
- Use WebSocket for real-time features (not polling)
- Cache AI responses where appropriate
- Minimize page content extraction token usage

### User Experience
- Always provide loading states
- Show error messages that help users
- Make all interactive elements keyboard accessible
- Test on mobile devices
- Provide visual feedback for all actions
- Stream AI responses for better perceived performance

